import React from 'react';
import { Typography } from '@material-ui/core';
import {Grid} from '@material-ui/core';
import Project from './Project.js';


const Projects = () => {
      
    return (
        <Grid container
        direction="row"
        justify="center"
        alignItems="center"
        style={{marginLeft:'30px', paddingRight:'30px', height:'400px', backgroundColor:'rgba(0,0,0,0.7)'}}>

            <Grid item xs={4}>
                <Project 
                projectType='Coding Projects'/>
            </Grid>

            <Grid item xs={4}>
                <Project 
                projectType='Academic Projects'/>
            </Grid>

            <Grid item xs={4}
            style={{backgroundColor:'rgba(205, 255, 219,0.8)', height:'400px'}}>
            <Typography
                display="block"
                justifyContent="center"
                align="center"
                variant="h3"
                style={{opacity:'100%', fontWeight:'bold', fontSize:'40px', color:'black', marginTop:'25%'}}>
                    Projects
                </Typography>
            </Grid>

        </Grid>
            
    )
}

export default Projects;
